Perceptive Radio

The Perceptive Radio is a physical radio unit built as an extension to the Perceptive Media project from BBC R&D.

Ian Forrester's blog post about it:
http://cubicgarden.com/2013/05/22/perceptive-radio/

Built by:
BBC R&D - http://bbc.co.uk/rd - Ian Forrester, Tony Churnside, Jasmine Cox
MCQN Ltd - http://mcqn.com - Adrian McEwen, Patrick Fenner - http://def-proc.co.uk
Mudlark - http://wearemudlark.com - Greg Povey, Richard Birkin, James Rice


Perceptive Media

"It takes narrative back to something more aligned to a storyteller and a audience around a campfire using Internet technologies and sensibility to create something closer to a personal theater experience in your living room..."

BBC R&D Blog Post:
http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/researchanddevelopment/2012/07/breaking-out---an-audio-experi.shtml

